        },
        "subject": "LU-2456 lnet: Basic support for sysfs (user and kernel space)",
        "message": "LU-2456 lnet: Basic support for sysfs (user and kernel space)\n\nThis is an infrastructure addition to support the use of\nsysfs as a part of the Dynamic LNet Config project.\n\nSysfs is going to be the main way to communicate\nconfiguration changes to the LNet module.\n\nNote: the format of sysfs comamnds is: <pid>:<command>.\nThe \"<pid>:\" is put before the reply when you read\nthe sysfs file.  This wil help user-space code to\nwatch for collisions with other processes when writing\nto sysfs files (<pid> should match your own pid value).\n\nSigned-off-by: Doug Oucharek <doug.s.oucharek@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ifc16ab6b9b7b7e98e46cda2f23ef072f45d612c5\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
